WEBVTT

00:00.078 --> 00:01.487
Previously on Good Trouble...

00:01.488 --> 00:03.737
- How're you feeling about your pitch?
- I think it's great.

00:03.738 --> 00:04.868
A few of the women and I are

00:04.892 --> 00:06.257
putting together a spreadsheet

00:06.282 --> 00:07.737
that proves that
there's a gender pay gap.

00:07.738 --> 00:09.920
Did you really think a
password would keep me out?

00:09.945 --> 00:11.104
This is Viv.

00:11.129 --> 00:12.338
I think Viv is homeless.

00:12.363 --> 00:14.964
You don't know what the story is
with her dad, if there even is one.

00:14.988 --> 00:16.581
- You close with your brother?
- I wanna be.

00:16.605 --> 00:17.729
But he doesn't.

00:17.737 --> 00:19.236
And I'm working on forgiving you, too.

00:19.260 --> 00:21.964
- She's the only mother we got!
- I am not sorry!

00:21.989 --> 00:23.003
Dom?

00:23.028 --> 00:25.186
- When're you just gonna come out to your parents?
- Never.

00:25.187 --> 00:28.633
- I'm over Sumi.
- We are excited to get married.

00:28.658 --> 00:31.106
- She's not over you.
- You gonna tell me about Callie?

00:31.107 --> 00:32.747
Helping you with your piece last night?

00:32.773 --> 00:34.013
Did you hook up with her?

00:34.038 --> 00:35.254
So, I'm your boyfriend.

00:35.279 --> 00:36.736
They dropped the charges?

00:36.737 --> 00:38.236
He took a swing at a police officer.

00:38.237 --> 00:40.686
You were a shitty husband,
and a shitty father!

00:40.687 --> 00:42.976
I wish I was the one
who died that day, not Jacob.

00:48.357 --> 00:50.856
I want to thank everybody for comin' out

00:50.857 --> 00:53.154
to support Jamal and my family

00:53.977 --> 00:55.316
It is s my great honor

00:55.317 --> 00:56.899
to introduce one of the co-founders

00:56.924 --> 00:58.276
of Black Lives Matter...

00:58.277 --> 01:00.566
...Patrisse Cullors.

01:08.730 --> 01:11.396
Good morning, and
thank you for having me

01:11.397 --> 01:13.934
on such a tragic occasion.

01:13.959 --> 01:17.552
I want to send my deepest
condolences to Jamal's family,

01:18.333 --> 01:20.316
friends, and community.

01:20.317 --> 01:23.566
Jamal joins a running
list of black people killed

01:23.567 --> 01:24.776
by law enforcement.

01:24.777 --> 01:28.344
We are tired of burying our children.

01:28.369 --> 01:30.566
- "Forced out" why?
- There was an I.A. investigation

01:30.567 --> 01:32.186
goin' on about some comments

01:32.187 --> 01:33.643
he allegedly made to officers.

01:33.668 --> 01:36.356
One of which was that it's
cheaper for the department

01:36.357 --> 01:38.305
to let victims of police shootings die.

01:38.330 --> 01:40.066
- That's disgusting.
- There's more.

01:40.067 --> 01:41.776
Apparently, one of the officers present

01:41.777 --> 01:44.242
when Chief Kelley made the
comment, was one of the defendants

01:44.267 --> 01:46.857
in your case... Officer Griffin.

01:47.977 --> 01:50.155
Alicia Opal and I started

01:50.180 --> 01:52.194
Black Lives Matter five years ago

01:52.219 --> 01:54.141
- because we believe this country
- _

01:54.166 --> 01:56.106
- desperately needed to transform.
- _

01:56.107 --> 01:59.026
- Black Lives Matter!
- _

01:59.027 --> 02:01.575
Black Lives Matter!

02:01.600 --> 02:03.450
Jamal's life mattered!

02:03.475 --> 02:08.975
- Jamal's life mattered!
- Jamal's life mattered!

02:10.308 --> 02:12.896
Your mother has
suffered a brain aneurysm.

02:12.897 --> 02:16.026
The rupture caused severe
bleeding and stroke.

02:16.595 --> 02:18.095
There's no brain activity,

02:18.939 --> 02:21.525
and if we were to remove
life support now...

02:21.550 --> 02:23.447
she wouldn't be able
to breathe on her own.

02:24.291 --> 02:26.277
I don't believe that she's brain dead.

02:28.288 --> 02:30.413
It's just cheaper for you
to just let her die.

02:30.749 --> 02:32.106
A black woman with no money.

02:35.027 --> 02:36.496
They don't care about her life.

02:37.453 --> 02:39.082
I'm not pullin' the plug.

02:39.317 --> 02:41.019
I'm not lettin' them do that to her.

02:43.000 --> 02:49.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:51.187 --> 02:55.382
Black Lives Matter! Black Lives Matter!

03:28.438 --> 03:29.618
What is this?

03:29.643 --> 03:30.954
It's the salary information

03:31.477 --> 03:33.146
for all the men who work at Speckulate.

03:33.655 --> 03:35.405
Why are you giving this to me?

03:39.084 --> 03:42.584
- Am I interrupting anything?
- Nope, we are done.

03:45.722 --> 03:46.824
Everything okay?

03:47.097 --> 03:48.167
Yeah, fine.

03:48.527 --> 03:49.606
So, I've been, uh,

03:49.631 --> 03:51.857
thinking a lot about your Activism app.

03:51.882 --> 03:54.841
And I want to get started right
away, so I'm gonna give you

03:54.866 --> 03:57.285
a team of two engineers, a designer

03:57.317 --> 03:58.793
and an assistant, you can...

03:59.397 --> 04:00.816
choose whomever you want.

04:03.713 --> 04:04.776
That's not enough people.

04:04.777 --> 04:05.976
If you want more...

04:05.977 --> 04:07.612
No! That's amazing.

04:08.713 --> 04:11.587
Well... your... idea is amazing.

04:14.527 --> 04:16.680
- Uh, thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

04:17.228 --> 04:19.276
I should... get to work.

04:30.319 --> 04:32.106
Hey, all of this goes

04:32.107 --> 04:34.214
to the roof, but you have
to take the stairs. I'll help.

04:34.238 --> 04:36.846
Dennis, I'm going to keep
calling until you call me back.

04:36.871 --> 04:39.674
- I got it.
- And do not text me, I need to hear your voice!

04:39.699 --> 04:41.646
- Thanks! Nothing yet?
- No.

04:41.647 --> 04:44.050
I've called every jail and hospital.

04:44.527 --> 04:45.856
He's not in any of them.

04:45.881 --> 04:47.535
He's probably just on a banging bender

04:47.560 --> 04:50.430
with some 20-year-old
hot yoga teacher, right?

04:51.225 --> 04:53.105
- Hey, how was the protest?
- Good.

04:54.187 --> 04:55.976
Great seeing you there, by the way.

04:57.237 --> 04:58.896
Had a nail appointment.

04:58.897 --> 05:00.066
Dude...

05:00.067 --> 05:01.399
Did you see Malika?

05:01.424 --> 05:03.932
No, I didn't see her, but
there was a huge turnout.

05:04.357 --> 05:05.855
- Okay.
- God, I just don't understand why

05:05.879 --> 05:07.698
Dennis is putting us
all through this shit!

05:08.143 --> 05:09.174
Uh, Davia?

05:10.971 --> 05:12.106
I've heard much worse.

05:12.107 --> 05:13.818
Viv, what're you doing here?

05:14.229 --> 05:15.606
My dad's working late again.

05:15.607 --> 05:16.748
Can I hang here with you?

05:17.693 --> 05:18.977
Sure. Come on.

05:20.187 --> 05:22.857
Alice? I need you!

05:28.211 --> 05:29.258
How do I look?

05:32.027 --> 05:33.738
I think I'm still in love with you...

05:37.144 --> 05:39.054
Hey, I was looking for you.

05:41.533 --> 05:43.653
You look... beautiful.

05:47.216 --> 05:48.566
Alice...

05:48.567 --> 05:51.052
- I-I...
- Hey! Um...

05:51.528 --> 05:53.122
people have questions.

05:53.787 --> 05:55.564
I don't know anything, so...

05:56.493 --> 05:59.101
- So where's this wedding happening?
- Oh, everything's upstairs.

05:59.126 --> 06:00.376
On the roof, just go straight

06:00.401 --> 06:01.780
and the stairs are to your right.

06:01.805 --> 06:03.126
Who's getting married?

06:03.442 --> 06:04.952
Mom, Dad!

06:04.977 --> 06:07.418
Uh, what're you doing here...

06:07.443 --> 06:10.236
- ...today?
- We have an engagement present for Sumi.

06:10.261 --> 06:11.276
Sumi?

06:11.277 --> 06:13.760
- We were in the neighborhood.
- You live in Orange County.

06:13.785 --> 06:16.066
Every time we want to
come see where you live

06:16.067 --> 06:17.463
you make excuses,

06:17.870 --> 06:21.316
_

06:21.737 --> 06:23.128
Uh, look! Look!

06:23.698 --> 06:26.816
- What's there?
- Oh, I thought I saw a bat.

06:26.817 --> 06:28.580
- A bat?!
- You have bats?

06:28.605 --> 06:32.012
Well, Sumi's out of town, yeah,
you know, she's on vacation.

06:32.037 --> 06:33.908
So I'll make sure she gets this.

06:35.145 --> 06:37.355
So, what is this place?

06:37.380 --> 06:40.200
Well, we all have our own
apartments but we share

06:40.225 --> 06:41.895
a bathroom and a kitchen.

06:42.105 --> 06:43.186
Greetings.

06:43.187 --> 06:45.736
Boys and girls shower together?

06:45.761 --> 06:48.103
Well, not, like, together.

06:51.067 --> 06:52.936
Oh, hey.

06:52.937 --> 06:54.566
This is Jo...

06:54.567 --> 06:56.066
anna.

06:56.251 --> 06:57.516
She, um,

06:57.541 --> 06:58.646
is...

06:58.994 --> 07:01.026
She's someone who lives here.

07:01.027 --> 07:02.580
- Yes.
- Oh, hello.

07:02.605 --> 07:05.066
- Uh, hi, nice to meet you.
- Hello.

07:05.067 --> 07:06.564
You know what? I'm kinda busy,

07:06.589 --> 07:09.458
so, um, I'll make sure Sumi
gets this, and you two can just,

07:09.937 --> 07:11.533
- you know...
- Surprise!

07:11.558 --> 07:13.066
You're back!

07:13.067 --> 07:16.027
- So soon. How was your trip?
- What?

07:16.937 --> 07:19.526
Oh! Oh, great!

07:19.550 --> 07:21.236
_

07:21.237 --> 07:22.526
- San Francisco.
- San Diego.

07:22.527 --> 07:24.276
I knew it was San "Something."

07:24.277 --> 07:26.009
Those two get so mixed up.

07:26.298 --> 07:27.943
I have something for the bride.

07:29.146 --> 07:30.458
There she is!

07:30.483 --> 07:32.153
The bride, Meera.

07:33.054 --> 07:35.035
And Gael, the groom.

07:35.060 --> 07:37.461
Yes, ah, lovebirds, aren't
they cute, Mom and Dad?

07:37.486 --> 07:38.686
- Mm-hmm.
- Very nice.

07:38.710 --> 07:40.082
_

07:40.107 --> 07:43.026
- Congratulations.
- They're so in love!

07:44.057 --> 07:47.357
Yes... oh, yes, we are so in love.

07:49.067 --> 07:51.397
Mm. Mmm.

07:58.726 --> 08:00.524
We have to create it so we can feel

08:00.548 --> 08:02.077
proud of this country.

08:02.817 --> 08:07.106
So we can feel proud of
raising our children here,

08:07.691 --> 08:11.449
in this place that's
supposed to be free.

08:15.277 --> 08:16.936
You don't have to stay.

08:18.249 --> 08:21.958
I know it's hard to accept, but...

08:25.357 --> 08:26.717
Mom's gone.

08:29.326 --> 08:30.779
You'd be happy if she was dead.

08:31.826 --> 08:32.977
That's not true.

08:37.106 --> 08:38.417
I have somewhere I have to be.

08:38.442 --> 08:39.614
I'm sorry.

08:41.645 --> 08:42.686
But I'll be back?

08:58.544 --> 09:00.392
How do I know that you
aren't setting me up?

09:03.397 --> 09:04.743
When I took this job,

09:05.243 --> 09:07.399
they told me they wanted
to change the culture here.

09:08.246 --> 09:10.503
But, that was all B.S.

09:11.528 --> 09:13.682
The same B.S. I sold you on.

09:15.527 --> 09:17.907
I'd quit, but I'm a single
mom and I need the paycheck.

09:19.470 --> 09:21.857
I gave you that info to you because...

09:22.817 --> 09:25.056
the only way to force change around here

09:25.552 --> 09:27.340
is to publicly shame them.

09:29.083 --> 09:31.254
Please, no one can ever
know I gave that to you,

09:31.859 --> 09:34.543
or else I will never
work anywhere again.

09:37.027 --> 09:39.825
All rise for the
Honorable Judge Curtis Wilson.

09:48.567 --> 09:51.396
- Still can't believe he gave her your case.
- Thanks.

09:51.897 --> 09:52.936
Why not me?

09:53.147 --> 09:54.225
This totally sucks.

09:54.772 --> 09:55.816
You may be seated.

10:04.187 --> 10:05.236
That's hearsay.

10:05.237 --> 10:07.396
You can't prove Chief Kelley said that.

10:07.397 --> 10:08.816
And since he just passed away,

10:08.817 --> 10:10.356
you can't question him about it either.

10:10.357 --> 10:11.809
But you can prove

10:11.834 --> 10:13.154
Officer Griffin said he heard it.

10:13.996 --> 10:15.426
If I.A. questioned about it,

10:15.930 --> 10:17.290
it would be in his personnel file.

10:17.356 --> 10:19.236
Maybe that's why Wilson
wouldn't let us read it.

10:19.465 --> 10:22.653
If Griffin admitted to
being told that, by his boss?

10:23.098 --> 10:24.258
It goes straight to the failure

10:24.282 --> 10:25.867
to provide critical care complaint.

10:25.892 --> 10:28.316
But Wilson's already ruled
his personnel files stay out.

10:28.317 --> 10:29.384
It's not right!

10:29.937 --> 10:30.937
If it's in there,

10:31.204 --> 10:32.347
how could Wilson do that?

10:33.324 --> 10:35.764
Unless, that's how he got the
charges against his son dropped.

10:36.781 --> 10:37.983
Good afternoon.

10:38.008 --> 10:40.289
If everyone is ready, we'll
begin with opening statements.

10:49.187 --> 10:51.625
Jamal Thompson was shot

10:52.008 --> 10:53.646
seven times in the back,

10:53.851 --> 10:56.718
by Officer Griffin and Officer Turani.

10:57.677 --> 11:00.966
Merely because of the color of his skin.

11:01.530 --> 11:02.976
Because...

11:02.977 --> 11:04.897
some police are biased

11:05.913 --> 11:08.066
against men and women of color.

11:08.514 --> 11:09.526
Because...

11:09.527 --> 11:10.616
they could.

11:10.641 --> 11:12.845
Because there are police officers

11:12.870 --> 11:15.189
getting away with excessive use of force

11:15.214 --> 11:18.526
- every day in this country.
- Objection. Inflammatory.

11:18.527 --> 11:19.606
Sustained.

11:23.542 --> 11:24.698
Jamal Thompson...

11:25.011 --> 11:26.519
was arrested at 18

11:26.739 --> 11:27.778
for assault and battery.

11:27.803 --> 11:29.472
He was jumped by gang members.

11:29.497 --> 11:32.015
Officers will testify
that he was in a gang.

11:32.040 --> 11:34.132
Objection! Facts not in evidence.

11:34.157 --> 11:35.187
I'll allow it.

11:35.641 --> 11:38.038
Jamal was not in a gang.

11:38.063 --> 11:39.945
And not every young black man

11:40.156 --> 11:42.264
- is a gang member.
- Jamal matched

11:42.289 --> 11:43.616
the witness description

11:43.641 --> 11:47.236
of a 5'10" African-American
male wearing a red shirt

11:47.261 --> 11:48.646
who was breaking into cars.

11:48.647 --> 11:50.526
Not every witness reported the suspect

11:50.527 --> 11:52.212
to be wearing a red shirt.

11:52.237 --> 11:53.736
Why did he run if he was innocent?

11:53.737 --> 11:54.761
He was scared.

11:54.786 --> 11:56.867
He ran because he was guilty

11:56.892 --> 11:58.147
and afraid of getting caught.

11:58.148 --> 11:59.710
He was running away from them

11:59.735 --> 12:02.026
- when they shot him in the back.
- He turned...

12:02.027 --> 12:03.976
and lunged at them.
They thought he was armed.

12:03.977 --> 12:05.709
They were in fear for their lives.

12:05.734 --> 12:07.584
Does this look like a gun to you?

12:07.609 --> 12:08.976
Objection. Testifying.

12:08.977 --> 12:09.977
Sustained.

12:12.407 --> 12:13.688
And after they shot him,

12:15.063 --> 12:16.436
they let him lay there

12:16.907 --> 12:18.086
for 20 minutes,

12:18.687 --> 12:21.236
bleeding to death.

12:53.870 --> 12:55.912
Governor just signed
a bill granting access

12:55.937 --> 12:57.936
to the investigatory
records on officer conduct.

12:57.937 --> 12:59.913
That includes personnel files.

12:59.938 --> 13:01.381
There will still be exceptions,

13:01.406 --> 13:02.981
and until it takes effect in January,

13:03.006 --> 13:04.436
I'm bound by current law.

13:04.437 --> 13:06.476
Aren't you giving Jamal's
family grounds to appeal?

13:06.477 --> 13:08.792
No. Knowing what's in here,

13:08.817 --> 13:10.386
I'm confident that

13:10.411 --> 13:13.442
my ruling to keep Officer Griffin's
personnel records redacted

13:13.879 --> 13:15.262
will stand...

13:15.287 --> 13:16.527
even under the new law.

13:46.747 --> 13:50.912
_

13:50.937 --> 13:52.378
Thanks for letting me take a shower.

13:53.067 --> 13:54.156
Sure.

13:54.181 --> 13:55.575
It's good to have it done so

13:55.600 --> 13:58.026
when I get home, I won't
go to bed with wet hair.

13:58.434 --> 13:59.629
Where is "home"?

14:00.278 --> 14:01.316
Where do you live?

14:01.732 --> 14:02.976
Atwater Village.

14:02.977 --> 14:03.977
We have a house.

14:04.490 --> 14:05.693
So it's just you and your dad?

14:05.718 --> 14:06.786
Yeah...

14:06.811 --> 14:07.899
my mom died...

14:08.027 --> 14:09.106
a while ago.

14:09.623 --> 14:10.952
I'm really sorry to hear that.

14:11.357 --> 14:12.396
So...

14:12.397 --> 14:13.482
where's your boyfriend?

14:13.849 --> 14:14.937
Jeff?

14:16.357 --> 14:17.976
Ah, well, he doesn't live out here.

14:17.977 --> 14:19.526
He's back home in Wisconsin.

14:19.527 --> 14:21.936
- Are you guys serious?
- We are.

14:22.194 --> 14:25.896
But we have some pretty
big obstacles to overcome.

14:25.897 --> 14:28.375
Oh! My dad's here.

14:28.937 --> 14:30.856
Thanks for letting me hang out again.

14:30.857 --> 14:32.386
Why don't you ask your dad to come up?

14:33.187 --> 14:34.327
I'd like to meet him.

14:36.567 --> 14:39.566
I mean, the point is to change
the culture at Speckulate.

14:39.567 --> 14:42.736
Now that I have Evan's ear,
maybe I can have an impact on him.

14:42.737 --> 14:44.476
Maybe he didn't even
know about the pay gap.

14:44.477 --> 14:46.313
Maybe if I just talk to him about it,

14:46.338 --> 14:47.338
he'll fix it.

14:47.363 --> 14:49.894
And I'm getting to create
a social activism app.

14:50.218 --> 14:51.965
And I'm gonna hire Malika to consult.

14:52.402 --> 14:54.292
That could be a real change
in the world, where

14:54.754 --> 14:58.146
publishing the salary info could
just not have any effect at all.

14:58.356 --> 15:00.096
And it could just end
up getting me fired.

15:01.734 --> 15:02.976
What do you think I should do?

15:03.936 --> 15:05.184
Well...

15:08.147 --> 15:10.798
I think you can convince
yourself of almost anything.

15:11.756 --> 15:13.681
But your gut will always
tell you what's right.

15:15.298 --> 15:16.986
My gut tells me

15:17.369 --> 15:18.965
that my app will have
a more positive effect

15:18.989 --> 15:20.476
on changing the culture at Speckulate

15:20.477 --> 15:22.686
more than publishing the
salary information will.

15:22.687 --> 15:23.786
Well, there you go.

15:24.317 --> 15:26.397
Hey, this came for you earlier.

15:28.553 --> 15:30.027
So lucky I have you to talk to.

15:31.737 --> 15:33.177
How was your first day of the trial?

15:33.311 --> 15:34.857
Not sure.

15:39.187 --> 15:40.777
What's that?

15:42.027 --> 15:43.937
Uh, just a work thing.

15:46.313 --> 15:49.524
I am grateful to you for
taking care of my daughter.

15:50.376 --> 15:54.911
I work two jobs and they ask
me to stay late sometimes.

15:55.737 --> 15:58.477
I-I understand, I just
wanted to meet you.

15:59.780 --> 16:02.334
Uh, Viv says you have a home in Atwater?

16:03.436 --> 16:06.491
Is there any way she could take
the school bus after school?

16:06.999 --> 16:08.873
She seems mature
enough to be home alone.

16:11.477 --> 16:14.176
We, uh, did have a home.

16:14.777 --> 16:15.846
But...

16:16.647 --> 16:18.734
my wife was very sick

16:18.759 --> 16:20.921
and we lose our house.

16:22.607 --> 16:23.890
Where do you live now?

16:24.567 --> 16:26.652
I, um... saving

16:26.677 --> 16:28.794
for a deposit on an apartment.

16:29.966 --> 16:31.153
I hope to have enough soon.

16:31.716 --> 16:36.606
We're, uh-uh staying in shelters
and-and with friends when we can...

16:37.578 --> 16:38.736
Please...

16:39.024 --> 16:40.912
if you won't... call anyone.

16:41.929 --> 16:44.593
It is very hard as a single parent.

16:45.343 --> 16:46.648
Having to work so much.

16:49.155 --> 16:51.356
You know why I started with the drugs.

16:51.357 --> 16:54.186
