38:12.444 --> 38:13.614
be an idiot.

38:15.126 --> 38:16.493
It's not like I'd leave some big

38:17.133 --> 38:18.524
void in the world, but...

38:19.094 --> 38:20.755
it suddenly felt selfish,

38:20.780 --> 38:23.690
like a betrayal of Jacob.

38:26.694 --> 38:28.343
Who fought so hard to live.

38:33.099 --> 38:36.116
How would I explain that to him?

38:37.720 --> 38:38.883
If there is a heaven.

38:41.349 --> 38:42.466
How would I explain.

38:42.943 --> 38:44.155
We put him through so many

38:45.138 --> 38:46.905
tests and drug trials

38:47.373 --> 38:49.126
just to keep him with us.

38:53.713 --> 38:57.266
And then I just throw my life away?

39:05.493 --> 39:06.532
So, I...

39:09.530 --> 39:10.906
drove myself here.

39:12.850 --> 39:14.786
Checked in for a 48-hour hold.

39:19.536 --> 39:21.146
You lost your child.

39:24.771 --> 39:28.513
I can't imagine coping with
all that pain and grief.

39:29.435 --> 39:31.105
Especially when you keep it...

39:31.812 --> 39:33.651
locked up inside of yourself,

39:33.676 --> 39:35.784
and you won't share it with
anyone who cares about you.

39:35.808 --> 39:38.581
Because people do
care about you, Dennis.

39:39.620 --> 39:41.940
I know there would be a huge

39:41.965 --> 39:45.252
void in my life if you weren't here.

40:02.541 --> 40:04.298
I mean, there has to be someone in LA

40:04.323 --> 40:05.825
who needs a last-minute wedding cake.

40:05.826 --> 40:07.921
It's-it's delicious, super moist.

40:08.132 --> 40:09.639
Can I at least get store credit?

40:10.843 --> 40:12.566
Ugh. Hello?

40:15.536 --> 40:16.628
Hey!

40:17.081 --> 40:19.115
So, you guessed it.

40:19.116 --> 40:20.535
There is no more wedding.

40:20.536 --> 40:21.905
And, for the record,

40:21.906 --> 40:23.786
I had almost nothing to do with it.

40:27.368 --> 40:28.535
What's wrong?

40:29.486 --> 40:31.906
This isn't working... for me.

40:33.597 --> 40:34.785
I mean...

40:35.027 --> 40:37.924
was it because of what happened
with my parents yesterday or...?

40:37.949 --> 40:40.724
Well, that was kinda ridiculous.

40:42.334 --> 40:44.420
Why did you introduce me as "Joanna"

40:44.616 --> 40:46.818
and tell your parents that
I live here at The Coterie?

40:47.545 --> 40:49.324
I don't know, it just kind of flew out.

40:49.349 --> 40:51.146
Okay, well, I think I know why.

40:52.115 --> 40:53.305
It's 'cause I look gay.

40:54.400 --> 40:56.256
So, if I'm your friend

40:56.281 --> 40:58.353
then you're guilty by association.

40:59.189 --> 41:01.596
- No...
- Whereas Sumi passes as straight,

41:02.524 --> 41:03.785
so it was never an issue.

41:03.786 --> 41:05.955
- N-no, that's not why...
- Alice.

41:05.956 --> 41:07.405
Look.

41:07.406 --> 41:08.776
Okay, we're sitting.

41:09.971 --> 41:11.057
I don't think...

41:11.581 --> 41:15.253
that the problem is just that
you're not out to your parents.

41:16.326 --> 41:17.405
It's you're not...

41:17.406 --> 41:19.610
out to yourself.

41:21.045 --> 41:22.414
You're not at peace

41:23.270 --> 41:24.366
with being gay.

41:27.019 --> 41:28.690
And that's way scarier.

41:29.956 --> 41:31.808
'Cause if you can't accept yourself...

41:33.792 --> 41:35.162
how can you accept me?

41:41.996 --> 41:44.325
I'm voting there's maple frosting.

41:44.326 --> 41:45.615
I think it's pecan.

41:46.250 --> 41:47.555
I'm so tired.

41:48.166 --> 41:51.035
Wait, did they really just
stop the trial for a whole day?

41:51.036 --> 41:52.075
Yeah.

41:52.576 --> 41:54.536
And did we ever find out
what the new evidence is?

41:54.996 --> 41:56.116
Nope.

41:58.166 --> 42:00.206
- What's gonna happen with your app?
- I don't know.

42:01.235 --> 42:02.399
I mean, if I leave Speckulate,

42:02.423 --> 42:05.281
we can't keep it, and if I do stay,

42:05.306 --> 42:06.905
things could get weird with my boss

42:06.906 --> 42:08.906
who I think is interested
in more than just my app.

42:09.097 --> 42:10.176
Gross.

42:10.201 --> 42:11.951
- Ugh.
- Evan?

42:14.091 --> 42:16.705
Hey, has... has anyone
heard from Dennis?

42:16.706 --> 42:19.325
Uh, yeah, he finally called me back.

42:19.326 --> 42:21.365
He decided to take a road trip.

42:21.366 --> 42:24.285
- And he's had really bad reception.
- Mmm.

42:24.286 --> 42:25.825
Hey, where's Joey?

42:26.458 --> 42:27.903
Uh... working.

42:28.723 --> 42:29.825
She had a...

42:29.826 --> 42:32.285
- shift that just came up.
- By the way,

42:32.598 --> 42:34.995
I'm not moving back to Wisconsin.

42:34.996 --> 42:37.293
I've decided to sign
on for another year,

42:37.318 --> 42:38.817
and get my masters in teaching.

42:39.037 --> 42:41.587
- Yes!
- Here, here!

42:41.612 --> 42:42.731
Thanks.

42:42.927 --> 42:44.711
I'd like to make another toast.

42:44.736 --> 42:46.445
To The Coterie at the Palace.

42:46.470 --> 42:48.865
"An intentional community." Hm...

42:48.866 --> 42:51.707
"... where we share resources to

42:51.732 --> 42:54.260
enrich our lives and the lives..."

42:54.285 --> 42:56.229
"... of others by
cultivating friendship,

42:56.254 --> 42:57.365
social progress..."

42:57.366 --> 42:58.865
"... and artistic expression."

42:58.866 --> 43:00.955
I've never been more proud.

43:00.956 --> 43:02.104
You know I wrote it myself.

43:02.129 --> 43:04.479
- To The Coterie.
- To The Coterie!

43:15.826 --> 43:17.405
- Hello?
- Hey, Mom.

43:17.406 --> 43:18.606
- Um...
- Alice?

43:19.200 --> 43:21.707
- Why you call so late?
- Can you put Dad on, too?

43:22.231 --> 43:23.614
Okay, hold on.

43:23.864 --> 43:25.629
No, I don't... I don't want...

43:26.521 --> 43:28.239
I'm not trying to FaceTime.

43:28.264 --> 43:29.264
Okay.

43:30.131 --> 43:31.286
What's wrong?

43:32.906 --> 43:34.786
Nothing's wrong.

43:37.249 --> 43:39.467
There's just something
that I need to tell you.

43:40.858 --> 43:42.389
Did Sumi get married?

43:43.014 --> 43:45.178
Is that why you're crying?

43:46.209 --> 43:47.412
What do you mean?

43:47.437 --> 43:51.221
- To that girl Meera?
- Is your heart broken?

43:54.509 --> 43:55.579
Um...

43:56.587 --> 43:58.111
why would my heart be broken?

43:59.233 --> 44:00.311
Because...

44:01.350 --> 44:02.491
you loved her.

44:07.764 --> 44:10.205
How did... I mean...

44:10.206 --> 44:12.709
you knew?

44:14.006 --> 44:15.995
We've known for a long time.

44:15.996 --> 44:18.855
We've just been waiting
for you to tell us.

44:19.456 --> 44:21.326
We love you, Alice.

44:22.814 --> 44:26.665
We still want you to get
married, and have grandchildren.

44:28.706 --> 44:31.365
That, uh, Joanna seems nice.

44:40.812 --> 44:45.460
_

44:58.826 --> 45:02.115
Hey.

45:06.866 --> 45:08.866
What're you doing here?

45:10.803 --> 45:12.222
I thought you were back home.

45:12.247 --> 45:13.446
I was.

45:14.666 --> 45:17.666
But then I flew back because
I wanted to tell you in person.

45:19.317 --> 45:20.419
I left Lily.

45:23.831 --> 45:24.970
Well, I'm beat.

45:25.996 --> 45:28.496
- Good night, ladies.
- Good night.

45:34.406 --> 45:35.996
So...

45:37.996 --> 45:39.280
I did a thing today.

45:40.999 --> 45:43.115
I can't believe you
took the fall for Angela.

45:43.641 --> 45:44.704
You know, you're a...

45:45.724 --> 45:46.899
pretty amazing person.

45:48.406 --> 45:50.785
Well, you stood up there with us.

45:50.786 --> 45:52.285
Talk about amazingness.

45:55.401 --> 45:58.955
You know, I know we're
colleagues, and...

45:58.956 --> 46:03.215
I don't want you to think I don't
respect you as a brilliant engineer

46:03.790 --> 46:04.931
but...

46:05.533 --> 46:07.264
do you mind if I kiss you?

46:10.786 --> 46:13.035
Uh, yeah, that would kinda
be really disrespectful

46:13.036 --> 46:14.825
and inappropriate...

46:14.826 --> 46:16.785
I'm so kidding, please kiss me.

46:16.786 --> 46:18.206
Please.

46:28.286 --> 46:29.575
Oh, my God.

46:29.576 --> 46:31.996
I know.

46:34.496 --> 46:35.614
So...

46:36.997 --> 46:38.141
what're you gonna do?

46:38.786 --> 46:39.848
About what?

46:40.825 --> 46:42.095
Who are you gonna choose?

46:43.379 --> 46:45.645
Jamie or Gael?

